onMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### `src/index.ts`\nExports the public API:\n- **Types**: `User`, `CreateUserInput`, `UserFilters`, `Role`, `Permission`\n- **User Management**: `registerUser`, `validateUser`, `getUserById`, `getAllUsers`, `canUserPerformAction`, `getDefaultConnection`, `resetDefaultConnection`\n- **Validation**: `createUserSchema`, `userIdSchema`, `userFiltersSchema`, `roleSchema`, `validateCreateUser`, `validateUserId`\n- **Database**: `createDatabase`, `createTables`, `insertUser`, `findUserById`, `findAllUsers`, `DatabaseConnection`\n- **Permissions**: `hasPermission`, `getAllPermissions`, `canManageUsers`, `canWrite`, `canDelete`, `requirePermission`\n\n#### `src/types.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { getUserById } from './user.js';\n\nexport type Role = 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer';\nexport type Permission = 'read' | 'write' | 'delete' | 'manage_users' | 'view_reports';\n\nexport interface User {\n  id: number;\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n  role: Role;\n  createdAt: string;\n  updatedAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CreateUserInput {\n  name: string;\n  email: string;\n  role: Role;\n}\n\nexport interface UserFilters {\n  role?: Role;\n  search?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  offset?: number;\n}\n\nexport function userExists(id: number): boolean {\n  return getUserById(id) !== null;\n}\n```\n\n#### `src/database.ts`\nImplements SQLite database:\n- `createDatabase(path)` - creates DB connection\n- `createTables(conn)` - creates users table with indexes\n- `insertUser(conn, user)` - inserts and returns user\n- `findUserById(conn, id)` - queries by ID\n- `findAllUsers(conn)` - queries all users\n- Uses better-sqlite3 with WAL mode and foreign key constraints\n\n#### `src/user.ts`\nUser management with default connection:\n- `getDefaultConnection()` - lazy-loads in-memory SQLite\n- `resetDefaultConnection()` - closes and resets for tests\n- `registerUser(input)` - validates and creates user\n- `validateUser(input)` - returns validation result\n- `getUserById(id)` - retrieves user\n- `getAllUsers()` - lists all users\n- `canUserPerformAction(role, action)` - checks permissions\n\n#### `src/permissions.ts`\nRole-based access control (RBAC):\n```typescript\nconst ROLE_PERMISSIONS: Record<Role, Permission[]> = {\n  admin: ['read', 'write', 'delete', 'manage_users', 'view_reports'],\n  user: ['read', 'write', 'view_reports'],\n  viewer: ['read'],\n};\n```\n- `hasPermission(role, permission)` - checks if role has permission\n- `getAllPermissions(role)` - returns array of permissions\n- `canManageUsers(role)` - specific permission check\n- `canWrite(role)` - specific permission check\n- `canDelete(role)` - specific permission check\n- `requirePermission(role, permission)` - throws if not allowed\n\n#### `src/validation.ts`\nZod validation schemas:\n```typescript\nexport const roleSchema = z.enum(['admin', 'user', 'viewer']);\nexport const createUserSchema = z.object({\n  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),\n  email: z.string().email(),\n  role: roleSchema,\n});\nexport const userIdSchema = z.string().pipe(\n  z.coerce.number().int().positive()\n);\nexport const userFiltersSchema = z.object({\n  role: roleSchema.optional(),\n  search: z.string().optional(),\n  limit: z.string().pipe(z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100)).optional(),\n  offset: z.string().pipe(z.coerce.number().int().min(0)).optional(),\n});\n```\n\n#### Core Tests\n- **user.test.ts**: Tests user registration, retrieval, listing, validation\n- **permissions.test.ts**: Tests RBAC for all roles and permission checks\n- **validation.test.ts**: Tests Zod schemas, string-to-number coercion via z.pipe()\n\n---\n\n### **packages/api - Express HTTP API**\n\n#### `package.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@monorepo/api\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./dist/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"start\": \"node dist/index.js\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@monorepo/core\": \"*\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### `tsconfig.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"composite\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"../core\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### `src/index.ts`\nExpress app setup:\n- Creates Express app with JSON middleware\n- `/health` - health check endpoint\n- `/auth` - public authentication routes\n- `/users` - protected user CRUD routes with auth middleware\n- Global error handler with 500 response\n\n#### `src/middleware/auth.ts`\nAuthentication and permission middleware:\n- `authMiddleware` - checks for Bearer token or x-user-role header\n- `requirePermissionMiddleware(permission)` - factory for permission checks\n- Returns 401 for missing auth, 403 for insufficient permissions\n\n#### `src/routes/auth.ts`\nAuthentication endpoints:\n- `POST /register` - self-registration with forced 'user' role\n- `POST /login` - simplified mock login (any email accepted)\n- `GET /verify` - verifies token format (mock-token-*)\n\n#### `src/routes/users.ts`\nUser CRUD endpoints:\n- `GET /` - lists all users\n- `GET /:id` - gets user by ID with validation\n- `POST /` - creates user (requires admin role)\n- `DELETE /:id` - deletes user (requires admin role)\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This file imports `createUser` from `@monorepo/core` (line 7) **BUT THIS EXPORT DOESN'T EXIST**. Should use `registerUser` instead.\n\n#### `tests/auth.test.ts`\nTests all auth endpoints with mock tokens and various scenarios.\n\n#### `tests/users.test.ts`\n**HAS UNRESOLVED MERGE CONFLICT MARKERS (lines 14-28)**\n```\n<<<<<<< HEAD\n  it('creates user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n=======\n  it('registers user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com', role: 'user' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n>>>>>>> refactor/user-system\n```\n\nTests user CRUD operations with permission checks.\n\n---\n\n### **packages/worker - Background Job Scheduler**\n\n#### `package.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@monorepo/worker\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./dist/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"start\": \"node dist/index.js\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@monorepo/core\": \"*\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### `tsconfig.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"composite\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"../core\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### `src/index.ts`\nWorker entry point:\n- Creates scheduler and registers jobs\n- `sync` job - runs every 60 seconds\n- `cleanup` job - runs every 5 minutes\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGINT\n\n#### `src/scheduler.ts`\nJob scheduler implementation:\n```typescript\ninterface JobDefinition {\n  name: string;\n  handler: () => Promise<void> | void;\n  intervalMs: number;\n  timer?: ReturnType<typeof setInterval>;\n  lastRun?: Date;\n  runCount: number;\n  errors: string[];\n}\n\nclass Scheduler {\n  register(name, handler, intervalMs)\n  start()\n  stop()\n  async runOnce(name)\n  getStatus() - returns job status array\n  isRunning()\n}\n```\n\n#### `src/jobs/sync.ts`\n**ISSUE**: Imports `createUser` from `@monorepo/core` (line 7) **BUT THIS DOESN'T EXIST**. Should use `registerUser`.\n\nFunctionality:\n- `fetchExternalUsers()` - simulated external data source\n- `syncJob()` - syncs external users, skips duplicates by email\n- `syncSingleUser(userId)` - syncs single user by ID\n\n#### `src/jobs/cleanup.ts`\nMaintenance job:\n- `cleanupJob()` - identifies stale records (>365 days old)\n- `getCleanupThresholdDays()` - returns threshold\n- Returns cleanup stats (staleRecords, cleanedUp, duration)\n\n#### Worker Tests\n- **scheduler.test.ts**: Tests job registration, running, tracking\n- **cleanup.test.ts**: Tests cleanup job execution\n- **sync.test.ts**: Tests data sync, deduplication, single user sync\n\n---\n\n### **Root Tests**\n\n#### `tests/structural.test.ts`\nValidation tests:\n1. **Circular dependency check** - uses madge tool\n2. **Merge conflict markers** - scans all TS files for `<<<<<<<`, `=======`, `>>>>>>>`\n3. **.env file secrets** - checks for PASSWORD, SECRET, TOKEN, API_KEY\n4. **Build validation** - runs `tsc -b --force`\n5. **TypeScript strict mode** - verifies strict: true in all packages\n\n---\n\n## **CRITICAL ISSUES FOUND**\n\n### 1. **CIRCULAR DEPENDENCY in packages/core** ⚠️\n**Location**: `packages/core/src/types.ts` → `packages/core/src/user.ts` → `packages/core/src/types.ts`\n\n**Problem**:\n- `types.ts` line 5: `import { getUserById } from './user.js';`\n- `user.ts` line 5: `import type { User, CreateUserInput } from './types.js';`\n\n**Impact**: This creates a circular import dependency. While TypeScript may handle it due to the `import type` in user.ts, it's fragile and violates best practices.\n\n### 2. **MISSING FUNCTION EXPORT** from `packages/core/src/index.ts` ⚠️\n**Problem**:\n- `packages/api/src/routes/users.ts` line 7 imports `createUser` from `@monorepo/core`\n- `packages/worker/src/jobs/sync.ts` line 7 imports `createUser` from `@monorepo/core`\n- **But `createUser` is NOT exported** from `packages/core/src/index.ts`\n- The function that exists is `registerUser` (exported from `packages/core/src/user.ts`)\n\n**Impact**: \n- Both API and Worker will fail at runtime with \"createUser is not exported\"\n- This will break the user creation endpoints and sync job\n- The correct function should be `registerUser`\n\n### 3. **UNRESOLVED MERGE CONFLICT** in `packages/api/tests/users.test.ts` ⚠️\n**Location**: Lines 14-28\n\n**Conflict**:\n```\n<<<<<<< HEAD\n  it('creates user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n=======\n  it('registers user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com', role: 'user' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n>>>>>>> refactor/user-system\n```\n\n**Impact**:\n- Test file is syntactically invalid\n- Tests cannot run\n- The conflict is between HEAD (creates without role) and refactor/user-system (requires role)\n\n### 4. **SECRETS IN .env FILE** ⚠️\n**Location**: `/workspace/.env`\n\n**Problem**:\n- File contains database credentials:\n  - `DB_PASSWORD=super_secret_password_123`\n  \n**Impact**:\n- This violates security best practices\n- Should be in `.gitignore`\n- The structural test expects no PASSWORD/SECRET/TOKEN/API_KEY in .env files\n\n---\n\n## **Dependency Graph**\n\n```\npackages/core\n  ├── depends on: zod, better-sqlite3\n  └── exports: types, user management, validation, database, permissions\n\npackages/api\n  ├── depends on: @monorepo/core, express\n  ├── references: packages/core (tsconfig)\n  └── exports: createApp function\n\npackages/worker\n  ├── depends on: @monorepo/core\n  ├── references: packages/core (tsconfig)\n  └── exports: createWorker function\n```\n\n---\n\n## **Summary**\n\nThis is a 3-package TypeScript monorepo with a **core library**, an **Express API**, and a **background worker** scheduler. It demonstrates a typical monorepo structure with shared code, dependent packages, and tests. However, it has 4 critical issues:\n\n1. **Circular dependency** between `types.ts` and `user.ts` in core\n2. **Missing export** of `createUser` (should be `registerUser`) - breaks API and Worker\n3. **Unresolved merge conflict** in API tests - blocks test execution\n4. **Secrets in .env file** - security violation\n\nAll configuration files are properly set up with TypeScript strict mode, workspace configuration, and proper tsconfig references."}],"totalDurationMs":101119,"totalTokens":43440,"totalToolUseCount":55,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":326,"cache_read_input_tokens":37604,"output_tokens":5510,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":326,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
